{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1240,"text":"A few years ago,\nI broke into my own house."},{"time":4880,"text":"I had just driven home,"},{"time":6120,"text":"it was around midnight\nin the dead of Montreal winter,"},{"time":8680,"text":"I had been visiting my friend,\nJeff, across town,"},{"time":11000,"text":"and the thermometer on the front porch\nread minus 40 degrees --"},{"time":15800,"text":"and don't bother asking\nif that's Celsius or Fahrenheit,"},{"time":18920,"text":"minus 40 is where the two scales meet --"},{"time":21400,"text":"it was very cold."},{"time":22680,"text":"And as I stood on the front porch\nfumbling in my pockets,"},{"time":25920,"text":"I found I didn't have my keys."},{"time":28200,"text":"In fact, I could see them\nthrough the window,"},{"time":30320,"text":"lying on the dining room table\nwhere I had left them."},{"time":33440,"text":"So I quickly ran around\nand tried all the other doors and windows,"},{"time":36600,"text":"and they were locked tight."},{"time":38200,"text":"I thought about calling a locksmith --\nat least I had my cellphone,"},{"time":41367,"text":"but at midnight, it could take a while\nfor a locksmith to show up,"},{"time":44720,"text":"and it was cold."},{"time":48421,"text":"I couldn't go back to my friend\nJeff's house for the night"},{"time":51160,"text":"because I had an early flight\nto Europe the next morning,"},{"time":53851,"text":"and I needed to get\nmy passport and my suitcase."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56400,"text":"So, desperate and freezing cold,"},{"time":58920,"text":"I found a large rock and I broke\nthrough the basement window,"},{"time":62560,"text":"cleared out the shards of glass,"},{"time":64560,"text":"I crawled through,"},{"time":65920,"text":"I found a piece of cardboard\nand taped it up over the opening,"},{"time":69360,"text":"figuring that in the morning,\non the way to the airport,"},{"time":72004,"text":"I could call my contractor\nand ask him to fix it."},{"time":74800,"text":"This was going to be expensive,"},{"time":76301,"text":"but probably no more expensive\nthan a middle-of-the-night locksmith,"},{"time":79880,"text":"so I figured, under the circumstances,\nI was coming out even."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84920,"text":"Now, I'm a neuroscientist by training"},{"time":87120,"text":"and I know a little bit\nabout how the brain performs under stress."},{"time":91240,"text":"It releases cortisol\nthat raises your heart rate,"},{"time":94800,"text":"it modulates adrenaline levels"},{"time":97080,"text":"and it clouds your thinking."},{"time":99080,"text":"So the next morning,"},{"time":101080,"text":"when I woke up on too little sleep,"},{"time":103560,"text":"worrying about the hole in the window,"},{"time":106320,"text":"and a mental note\nthat I had to call my contractor,"},{"time":109120,"text":"and the freezing temperatures,"},{"time":110840,"text":"and the meetings I had upcoming in Europe,"},{"time":113320,"text":"and, you know, with all\nthe cortisol in my brain,"},{"time":116880,"text":"my thinking was cloudy,"},{"time":118280,"text":"but I didn't know it was cloudy\nbecause my thinking was cloudy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121720,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":123240,"text":"And it wasn't until I got\nto the airport check-in counter,"},{"time":126520,"text":"that I realized I didn't have my passport."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128800,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":130840,"text":"So I raced home in the snow\nand ice, 40 minutes,"},{"time":134320,"text":"got my passport,\nraced back to the airport,"},{"time":136800,"text":"I made it just in time,"},{"time":138640,"text":"but they had given away\nmy seat to someone else,"},{"time":140903,"text":"so I got stuck in the back of the plane,\nnext to the bathrooms,"},{"time":143903,"text":"in a seat that wouldn't recline,\non an eight-hour flight."},{"time":147880,"text":"Well, I had a lot of time to think\nduring those eight hours and no sleep."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151360,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":152520,"text":"And I started wondering,\nare there things that I can do,"},{"time":155200,"text":"systems that I can put into place,"},{"time":157160,"text":"that will prevent bad things\nfrom happening?"},{"time":159640,"text":"Or at least if bad things happen,"},{"time":161560,"text":"will minimize the likelihood\nof it being a total catastrophe."},{"time":167360,"text":"So I started thinking about that,"},{"time":168960,"text":"but my thoughts didn't crystallize\nuntil about a month later."},{"time":171842,"text":"I was having dinner with my colleague,\nDanny Kahneman, the Nobel Prize winner,"},{"time":175560,"text":"and I somewhat embarrassedly told him\nabout having broken my window,"},{"time":178960,"text":"and, you know, forgotten my passport,"},{"time":181400,"text":"and Danny shared with me"},{"time":182640,"text":"that he'd been practicing\nsomething called prospective hindsight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187160,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":188920,"text":"It's something that he had gotten\nfrom the psychologist Gary Klein,"},{"time":192087,"text":"who had written about it\na few years before,"},{"time":194160,"text":"also called the pre-mortem."},{"time":196280,"text":"Now, you all know what the postmortem is."},{"time":198257,"text":"Whenever there's a disaster,"},{"time":199760,"text":"a team of experts come in and they try\nto figure out what went wrong, right?"},{"time":204080,"text":"Well, in the pre-mortem, Danny explained,"},{"time":206520,"text":"you look ahead and you try to figure out\nall the things that could go wrong,"},{"time":210440,"text":"and then you try to figure out\nwhat you can do"},{"time":213040,"text":"to prevent those things from happening,\nor to minimize the damage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216560,"text":"So what I want to talk to you about today"},{"time":219520,"text":"are some of the things we can do\nin the form of a pre-mortem."},{"time":223080,"text":"Some of them are obvious,\nsome of them are not so obvious."},{"time":226000,"text":"I'll start with the obvious ones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227960,"text":"Around the home, designate a place\nfor things that are easily lost."},{"time":233680,"text":"Now, this sounds\nlike common sense, and it is,"},{"time":237560,"text":"but there's a lot of science\nto back this up,"},{"time":240120,"text":"based on the way our spatial memory works."},{"time":243440,"text":"There's a structure in the brain\ncalled the hippocampus,"},{"time":246320,"text":"that evolved over tens\nof thousands of years,"},{"time":249280,"text":"to keep track of the locations\nof important things --"},{"time":253080,"text":"where the well is,\nwhere fish can be found,"},{"time":255520,"text":"that stand of fruit trees,"},{"time":258040,"text":"where the friendly and enemy tribes live."},{"time":260680,"text":"The hippocampus is the part of the brain"},{"time":262609,"text":"that in London taxicab drivers\nbecomes enlarged."},{"time":266120,"text":"It's the part of the brain\nthat allows squirrels to find their nuts."},{"time":269840,"text":"And if you're wondering,\nsomebody actually did the experiment"},{"time":272722,"text":"where they cut off\nthe olfactory sense of the squirrels,"},{"time":275520,"text":"and they could still find their nuts."},{"time":277360,"text":"They weren't using smell,\nthey were using the hippocampus,"},{"time":280200,"text":"this exquisitely evolved mechanism\nin the brain for finding things."},{"time":285240,"text":"But it's really good for things\nthat don't move around much,"},{"time":289000,"text":"not so good for things that move around."},{"time":291480,"text":"So this is why we lose car keys\nand reading glasses and passports."},{"time":295800,"text":"So in the home,\ndesignate a spot for your keys --"},{"time":298320,"text":"a hook by the door,\nmaybe a decorative bowl."},{"time":301200,"text":"For your passport, a particular drawer."},{"time":303320,"text":"For your reading glasses,\na particular table."},{"time":306120,"text":"If you designate a spot\nand you're scrupulous about it,"},{"time":309600,"text":"your things will always be there\nwhen you look for them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312440,"text":"What about travel?"},{"time":313680,"text":"Take a cell phone picture\nof your credit cards,"},{"time":316080,"text":"your driver's license, your passport,"},{"time":318400,"text":"mail it to yourself so it's in the cloud."},{"time":320680,"text":"If these things are lost or stolen,\nyou can facilitate replacement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325080,"text":"Now these are some rather obvious things."},{"time":327720,"text":"Remember, when you're under stress,\nthe brain releases cortisol."},{"time":331280,"text":"Cortisol is toxic,\nand it causes cloudy thinking."},{"time":334520,"text":"So part of the practice of the pre-mortem"},{"time":337080,"text":"is to recognize that under stress\nyou're not going to be at your best,"},{"time":341360,"text":"and you should put systems in place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343680,"text":"And there's perhaps\nno more stressful a situation"},{"time":346640,"text":"than when you're confronted\nwith a medical decision to make."},{"time":350080,"text":"And at some point, all of us\nare going to be in that position,"},{"time":353400,"text":"where we have to make\na very important decision"},{"time":355800,"text":"about the future of our medical care\nor that of a loved one,"},{"time":359120,"text":"to help them with a decision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360800,"text":"And so I want to talk about that."},{"time":362440,"text":"And I'm going to talk about\na very particular medical condition."},{"time":365480,"text":"But this stands as a proxy for all kinds\nof medical decision-making,"},{"time":369040,"text":"and indeed for financial decision-making,\nand social decision-making --"},{"time":373080,"text":"any kind of decision you have to make"},{"time":375360,"text":"that would benefit from a rational\nassessment of the facts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379400,"text":"So suppose you go to your doctor\nand the doctor says,"},{"time":382560,"text":"\"I just got your lab work back,\nyour cholesterol's a little high.\""},{"time":387240,"text":"Now, you all know that high cholesterol"},{"time":390280,"text":"is associated with an increased risk\nof cardiovascular disease,"},{"time":394440,"text":"heart attack, stroke."},{"time":395880,"text":"And so you're thinking"},{"time":397120,"text":"having high cholesterol\nisn't the best thing,"},{"time":399240,"text":"and so the doctor says,\n\"You know, I'd like to give you a drug"},{"time":402280,"text":"that will help you\nlower your cholesterol, a statin.\""},{"time":405080,"text":"And you've probably heard of statins,"},{"time":407000,"text":"you know that they're among\nthe most widely prescribed drugs"},{"time":409834,"text":"in the world today,"},{"time":411032,"text":"you probably even know\npeople who take them."},{"time":413135,"text":"And so you're thinking,\n\"Yeah! Give me the statin.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":415541,"text":"But there's a question\nyou should ask at this point,"},{"time":418000,"text":"a statistic you should ask for"},{"time":419880,"text":"that most doctors\ndon't like talking about,"},{"time":422360,"text":"and pharmaceutical companies\nlike talking about even less."},{"time":426800,"text":"It's for the number needed to treat."},{"time":429200,"text":"Now, what is this, the NNT?"},{"time":431200,"text":"It's the number of people\nthat need to take a drug"},{"time":434280,"text":"or undergo a surgery\nor any medical procedure"},{"time":437160,"text":"before one person is helped."},{"time":439560,"text":"And you're thinking,\nwhat kind of crazy statistic is that?"},{"time":442440,"text":"The number should be one."},{"time":443680,"text":"My doctor wouldn't prescribe\nsomething to me"},{"time":445760,"text":"if it's not going to help."},{"time":447069,"text":"But actually, medical practice\ndoesn't work that way."},{"time":449578,"text":"And it's not the doctor's fault,"},{"time":451134,"text":"if it's anybody's fault,\nit's the fault of scientists like me."},{"time":454077,"text":"We haven't figured out\nthe underlying mechanisms well enough."},{"time":456966,"text":"But GlaxoSmithKline estimates"},{"time":459400,"text":"that 90 percent of the drugs work\nin only 30 to 50 percent of the people."},{"time":464400,"text":"So the number needed to treat\nfor the most widely prescribed statin,"},{"time":468240,"text":"what do you suppose it is?"},{"time":470400,"text":"How many people have to take it\nbefore one person is helped?"},{"time":473240,"text":"300."},{"time":475075,"text":"This is according to research"},{"time":476480,"text":"by research practitioners\nJerome Groopman and Pamela Hartzband,"},{"time":480000,"text":"independently confirmed by Bloomberg.com."},{"time":482800,"text":"I ran through the numbers myself."},{"time":485920,"text":"300 people have to\ntake the drug for a year"},{"time":488320,"text":"before one heart attack, stroke\nor other adverse event is prevented."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492320,"text":"Now you're probably thinking,"},{"time":493725,"text":"\"Well, OK, one in 300 chance\nof lowering my cholesterol."},{"time":496560,"text":"Why not, doc? Give me\nthe prescription anyway.\""},{"time":498800,"text":"But you should ask at this point\nfor another statistic,"},{"time":501680,"text":"and that is, \"Tell me\nabout the side effects.\" Right?"},{"time":504280,"text":"So for this particular drug,"},{"time":505960,"text":"the side effects occur\nin five percent of the patients."},{"time":509640,"text":"And they include terrible things --"},{"time":511331,"text":"debilitating muscle and joint pain,\ngastrointestinal distress --"},{"time":515799,"text":"but now you're thinking, \"Five percent,"},{"time":517682,"text":"not very likely\nit's going to happen to me,"},{"time":519720,"text":"I'll still take the drug.\""},{"time":520982,"text":"But wait a minute."},{"time":522200,"text":"Remember under stress\nyou're not thinking clearly."},{"time":524560,"text":"So think about how you're going\nto work through this ahead of time,"},{"time":527750,"text":"so you don't have to manufacture\nthe chain of reasoning on the spot."},{"time":530973,"text":"300 people take the drug, right?\nOne person's helped,"},{"time":533489,"text":"five percent of those 300\nhave side effects,"},{"time":535920,"text":"that's 15 people."},{"time":537800,"text":"You're 15 times more likely\nto be harmed by the drug"},{"time":541720,"text":"than you are to be helped by the drug."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544560,"text":"Now, I'm not saying whether you\nshould take the statin or not."},{"time":547489,"text":"I'm just saying you should have\nthis conversation with your doctor."},{"time":550656,"text":"Medical ethics requires it,"},{"time":552000,"text":"it's part of the principle\nof informed consent."},{"time":554320,"text":"You have the right to have access\nto this kind of information"},{"time":557560,"text":"to begin the conversation about whether\nyou want to take the risks or not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561480,"text":"Now you might be thinking"},{"time":562720,"text":"I've pulled this number\nout of the air for shock value,"},{"time":565440,"text":"but in fact it's rather typical,\nthis number needed to treat."},{"time":568720,"text":"For the most widely performed surgery\non men over the age of 50,"},{"time":573360,"text":"removal of the prostate for cancer,"},{"time":575600,"text":"the number needed to treat is 49."},{"time":578200,"text":"That's right, 49 surgeries are done\nfor every one person who's helped."},{"time":582400,"text":"And the side effects in that case\noccur in 50 percent of the patients."},{"time":587080,"text":"They include impotence,\nerectile dysfunction,"},{"time":589960,"text":"urinary incontinence, rectal tearing,"},{"time":592760,"text":"fecal incontinence."},{"time":594240,"text":"And if you're lucky, and you're one\nof the 50 percent who has these,"},{"time":597760,"text":"they'll only last for a year or two."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600880,"text":"So the idea of the pre-mortem\nis to think ahead of time"},{"time":604520,"text":"to the questions\nthat you might be able to ask"},{"time":607080,"text":"that will push the conversation forward."},{"time":609480,"text":"You don't want to have to manufacture\nall of this on the spot."},{"time":612600,"text":"And you also want to think\nabout things like quality of life."},{"time":615520,"text":"Because you have a choice oftentimes,"},{"time":617320,"text":"do you I want a shorter life\nthat's pain-free,"},{"time":619640,"text":"or a longer life that might have\na great deal of pain towards the end?"},{"time":623440,"text":"These are things to talk about\nand think about now,"},{"time":625880,"text":"with your family and your loved ones."},{"time":627720,"text":"You might change your mind\nin the heat of the moment,"},{"time":630240,"text":"but at least you're practiced\nwith this kind of thinking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633320,"text":"Remember, our brain under stress\nreleases cortisol,"},{"time":637960,"text":"and one of the things\nthat happens at that moment"},{"time":640320,"text":"is a whole bunch on systems shut down."},{"time":642280,"text":"There's an evolutionary reason for this."},{"time":644209,"text":"Face-to-face with a predator,\nyou don't need your digestive system,"},{"time":647640,"text":"or your libido, or your immune system,"},{"time":650120,"text":"because if you're body is expending\nmetabolism on those things"},{"time":653800,"text":"and you don't react quickly,"},{"time":655480,"text":"you might become the lion's lunch,\nand then none of those things matter."},{"time":659480,"text":"Unfortunately,"},{"time":660920,"text":"one of the things that goes out the window\nduring those times of stress"},{"time":664560,"text":"is rational, logical thinking,"},{"time":666560,"text":"as Danny Kahneman\nand his colleagues have shown."},{"time":670000,"text":"So we need to train ourselves\nto think ahead"},{"time":673200,"text":"to these kinds of situations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675480,"text":"I think the important point here\nis recognizing that all of us are flawed."},{"time":681680,"text":"We all are going to fail now and then."},{"time":684560,"text":"The idea is to think ahead\nto what those failures might be,"},{"time":688200,"text":"to put systems in place\nthat will help minimize the damage,"},{"time":692120,"text":"or to prevent the bad things\nfrom happening in the first place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696280,"text":"Getting back to that\nsnowy night in Montreal,"},{"time":698960,"text":"when I got back from my trip,"},{"time":700720,"text":"I had my contractor install\na combination lock next to the door,"},{"time":704600,"text":"with a key to the front door in it,\nan easy to remember combination."},{"time":708160,"text":"And I have to admit,"},{"time":709400,"text":"I still have piles of mail\nthat haven't been sorted,"},{"time":712840,"text":"and piles of emails\nthat I haven't gone through."},{"time":715440,"text":"So I'm not completely organized,"},{"time":717240,"text":"but I see organization\nas a gradual process,"},{"time":720400,"text":"and I'm getting there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":721640,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":722880,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}